e Gensler . \"Gary Gensler has, for some reason, decided to take a war against crypto,\" Belshe states. \"Mr. Gensler wants to talk about use cases. Bitcoin is the strongest use case; it's a store of value unlike any other, it's a monetary system which is frankly a hedge against the dollar because the government here has had a really hard time containing costs.\" Related Videos 01:53 U.S. Strikes Deal With Mexico, Canada to Temporarily Delay Tariffs WSJ \u2022 11 minutes ago 03:11 US delays tariffs on Canada after 'good call' between Trump, Trudeau Yahoo Finance Video \u2022 30 minutes ago 04:37 The 'three-fold' applications of Trump's tariff strategy Yahoo Finance Video \u2022 1 hour ago 05:13 Retaliatory Tariffs on US Would Have Severe Impact: Smart Bloomberg \u2022 2 hours ago \"Bitcoin is a monetary system where it's a fixed supply, so you just don't have to worry about somebody deciding to spend the money [and] create a bunch of extra supply that wasn't anticipated,\" he adds. Catch Yahoo Finance Federal Reserve Reporter Jennifer Schonberger's full interview with outgoing SEC Chair Gary Gensler here . To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here . This post was written by Naomi Buchanan. View Comments Terms and Privacy Policy Privacy Dashboard Recommended Stories", "symbol": "CETH", "date": "2025-01-15T20:38:04", "sentiment": {"score": -0.0009001195430755615, "confidence": 0.10305724292993546, "probabilities": {"positive": 0.1021571233868599, "negative": 0.10305724292993546, "neutral": 0.7947856187820435}}, "embedding": [-0.1246606856584549, -0.02433147467672825, -0.03282090649008751, -0.047519851475954056, 0.07302699983119965, -0.0324929840862751, 0.058121807873249054, 0.022957386448979378, 0.05722266063094139, 0.052414003759622574, -0.08482656627893448, -0.00502042006701231, 0.04102689027786255, 0.03384743258357048, 0.03216775879263878, 0.00266443332657218, 0.0765044093132019, 0.02333051711320877, -